import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='x', color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['x'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['x'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of x-coordinates in the terrain?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('x-coordinates')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='lumosity', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['lumosity'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Lumosity: {:.2f}'.format(data['lumosity'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of lumosity values in the terrain?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    sns.countplot(x="name", data=data, palette="Set3")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of terrain types in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Terrain Type")
    plt.ylabel("Count")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
